01/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The situation in Serbian prisons is improving, according to David Diaz Jogeix, head of the human rights department at the OSCE mission in Serbia-Montenegro. Speaking at a meeting in Belgrade on Tuesday (30 September), Jogeix urged that prison personnel undergo additional training. He suggested that more be done to boost co-operation between the justice system and non-profit organisations.
In other news Tuesday, officials say a Serbian police officer went on a shooting rampage in Nis, killing four of his colleagues and wounding three others before being taken into custody by fellow officers. The gunman was identified as Vladimir Rovcanin. (Beta, Tanjug, BBC, AP, AFP - 30/09/03)
